statements.sql: select count(*) as aggregate from `jobs` inner join `seo` on `jobs`.`seo_id` = `seo`.`id` inner join `companies` as `co` on `jobs`.`company_id` = `co`.`id` where `co`.`is_approved` = 1 and `co`.`is_active` = 1 and `jobs`.`is_active` = 1 and `jobs`.`is_approved` = 1 and exists (select * from `seo` where `jobs`.`seo_id` = `seo`.`id` and json_contains(`seo`.`meta_keywords`, '\"Tech Insights\"'))
